p align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Maybe someone would know what to do....</span><hr size=1> You have alot of options available to you.  First, in most (if not all) states, it is rare that the father is given custody unless the mother can be shown to be unfit.  So, unless that applies, you could probably get the kids back if you want them and make him pay child support to you.  Secondly, it is illegal in most (if not all) states for a parent to deny access to the kids to the other parent unless there is a court order so ordering.  Furthermore, since he has a history of drug abuse, you probably have even greater leverage.<br>
<br>
You need to find a GOOD attorney.  I'm frankly quite surprised that your first attempt at working with an attorney yielded nothing.  Any half-decent attorney should be able to put the proper wheels in motion for you.  This all depends, of course, on your or your attorney's ability to track the guy and your kids down.  But if the guy has absconded across state lines with your kids, he could be prosecuted for child abduction as well.<br>
<br>
Bottom line... Get tough and get you a decent attorney! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caemus>Caemus</A> at: 8/9/03 6:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fvbeastlord>FVBeastLord</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lord of all the Wild</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/9/03 10:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1830.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Maybe someone would know what to do....</span><hr size=1> Well i'll add my 2 cents in, but im no lawyer. But i do know that what he did is against the law. Abduction threw visitation is not only immoral but illegal, its time you get a Good Attorney and go after him, if he is working someone has used his SSI Number for tax purposes and you can track him based of Employment records or by Credit check. Also an attorney can get a subpeina to get info on him threw the courts. You need to protect yourself and your children and deal with him immediately.<br>
